.. 387 \"LIKE THE SHEPHERD WHO PASTURES AROUND A SANCTUARY, ALL BUT GRAZING THEREIN. VERILY EVERY KING HAS A SANCTUARY AND ALLAH'S SANCTUARY IS HIS PROHIBITIONS.\" ...................... 388 \"IN THE BODY THERE IS A MORSEL OF FLESH WHICH, IF IT BE SOUND, ALL THE BODY IS SOUND AND WHICH, IF IT BE DISEASED, ALL OF IT IS DISEASED. THIS PART OF THE BODY IS THE HEART.\" .......... 390 SIGNS OF THE HEART .................................................................................................... 391 OTHER POINTS RELATED TO THIS HADITH ......................................................................... 393 SUMMARY OF THE HADITH ............................................................................................ 395 HADITH #7: \"THE RELIGION IS NASEEHAH\" ............................................................. 397 SELECTED VOCABULARY ................................................................................................ 397 TAKHREEJ ................................................................................................................... 397 GENERAL COMMENTS ABOUT THIS HADITH ...................................................................... 398 THE NARRATOR: TAMEEM AL-DAARI ............................................................................... 398 \"THE RELIGION IS THE NASEEHAH.11 ................................................................................. 398 \"To ALLAH\" ............................................................................................................... 402 \"To HIS BOOK\" ........................................................................................................... 403 11TO HIS MESSENGER\" .................................................................................................. 404 \"To THE LEADERS OF THE MUSLIMS\" ............................................................................... 405 \"To THE COMMON FOLK OF THE MUSLIMS\" .......................